HEADWORD: Dipnoi
<hw>Dip"no*i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ <?/ with two breathing apertures; <grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk>
twice + <?/ breath.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of ganoid
fishes, including the living genera <gen>Ceratodus</gen> and
<gen>Lepidosiren</gen>, which present the closest approximation to the
Amphibia. The air bladder acts as a lung, and the nostrils open inside
the mouth. See <er>Ceratodus</er>, and <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dipodomys</ent>⟦br⟧
